{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Fire}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/GO|species=Growlithe}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Fire|prevnum=057|prev=Primeape|nextnum=059|next=Arcanine|round=none}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Disambig|species=Growlithe}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Growlithe\n|jname=ガーディ\n|jtranslit=Gādi\n|tmname=Gardie\n|ndex=058\n|oldjdex=127\n|jdex=129\n|u2dex=051\n|adex=052\n|fbrow=144\n|abrow=065\n|typebox=1\n|type1=Fire\n|category=Puppy\n|height-ftin=2\'04"\n|height-m=0.7\n|weight-lbs=41.9\n|weight-kg=19.0\n|abilityn=d\n|ability1=Intimidate\n|ability2=Flash Fire\n|abilityd=Justified\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Field\n|eggcycles=20\n|evtotal=1\n|evat=1\n|expyield=70\n|oldexp=91\n|lv100exp=1,250,000\n|gendercode=63\n|color=Brown\n|catchrate=190\n|body=08\n|pokefordex=growlithe\n|generation=1\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Growlithe\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'ガーディ\'\'\' \'\'Gardie\'\') is a {{type|Fire}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation I]].\n\nIt [[Evolution|evolve]]s into {{p|Arcanine}} when exposed to a [[Fire Stone]].\n\n==Biology==\nGrowlithe is a quadruped, canine Pokémon. It has orange fur with black stripes along its back and legs. The fur on its muzzle, chest, belly, and tail is beige, as well as an additional tuft of fur on top of its head. Growlithe\'s coat is noticeably longer on its chest and tail. It has gray eyes, a black nose, and large, round ears with beige interiors. Its forepaws have two visible claws, while its hind paws have three toes each. Each paw has a brown pad.\n\nGrowlithe is a friendly and loyal Pokémon that will fearlessly defend its {{pkmn|Trainer}} and territory from harm, even against larger, stronger enemies. In particular, it has been known to fight with {{p|Rockruff}} over territory. It will fiercely bark at, bite, and chase away any perceived threat. Otherwise, this obedient Pokémon will wait motionlessly until given an order. It has a long history with people, as its bones have been found in Stone Age ruins. In the wild, Growlithe can be commonly found in {{DL|List of Pokémon by habitat|Grassland Pokémon|grassy plains}}.\n\nGrowlithe also has a powerful olfactory sense. If it detects an unknown smell in its territory, it roars to flush out the intruder. It is able to smell the emotions of others, and never forgets a scent. However, strong, unpleasant smells can disable its sense of smell for short periods, as seen in [[EP054|the anime]].\n\n==In the anime==\n===In the main series===\n[[File:Officer Jenny Growlithe.png|thumb|left|250px|Growlithe in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n====Major appearances====\n=====[[Growlie]]=====\n[[James]] had a pet Growlithe [[nickname]]d Growlie, which he owned as a child. However, he left it behind when he ran away from home. Despite this, it remains loyal to James.\n\n=====[[Officer Jenny\'s Growlithe]]=====\nGrowlithe and {{p|Arcanine|its evolved form}} have been frequently used as police dogs by [[Officer Jenny]] prior to the {{series|Best Wishes}}. A Growlithe also appeared in \'\'[[M21|The Power of Us]]\'\', which is set in a timeline different from the main series; it was under the ownership of the Officer Jenny of [[Fula City]].\n\n=====Other=====\nA Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[EP033|The Flame Pokémon-athon!]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Lara Laramie]]. It battled {{Ash}} while defending a {{p|Tauros}} from a ranch that he mistakenly tried to {{pkmn2|caught|catch}}.\n\nA Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[AG126|Saved by the Beldum]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Morrison]]. He used it in his battle against [[Gavin]], where it was defeated by {{p|Marowak}}. During his battle against Ash, Morrison\'s reluctance to fight his friend led Growlithe to be defeated by {{AP|Corphish}}.\n\nMultiple Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[AG139|On Cloud Arcanine]]\'\' as a whole litter taken care of by an Arcanine. [[Drew]] and {{an|May}} attempted to catch the Arcanine, but after finding the Growlithe litter, they decided to leave it alone.\n\nA Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[BW125|Cilan and the Case of the Purrloin Witness!]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Tedesco]]. Growlithe helped defend Ash and {{ashfr}} when [[Teaque]]\'s {{p|Vanillite}}\'s attacked them.\n\n====Minor appearances====\nGrowlithe debuted in \'\'[[EP030|Sparks Fly for Magnemite]]\'\', where it was seen in [[Gringey City]]\'s [[Pokémon Center]].\n\nA {{pkmn|Trainer}}\'s Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[M01|Mewtwo Strikes Back]]\'\' as one of the Pokémon {{OBP|Mewtwo|original series}} defeated while serving for {{an|Giovanni}}.\n\nA Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[PK01|Pikachu\'s Vacation]]\'\' as one of the Pokémon seen at the [[Pokémon Theme Park]].\n\nMultiple Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[EP065|Showdown at the Po-ké Corral]]\'\', where they were among the Pokémon living at [[Professor Oak\'s Laboratory]].\n\nA Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[EP086|Pikachu Re-Volts]]\'\', where it was among the Pokémon controlled by [[Cassidy]] and [[Butch]] at [[Mandarin Island North]].\n\nTwo Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[EP089|Shell Shock!]]\'\', under the ownership of an expedition crew led by [[Nurse Joy]], which was looking for {{p|Kabuto}} Fossils. They helped alert the group when boulders began to rain down on them.\n\nMultiple Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[M02|The Power of One]]\'\'.\n\nA Growlithe appeared in the Japanese credits of \'\'[[PK04|Pikachu\'s Rescue Adventure]]\'\'.\n\nA Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[EP124|Snubbull Snobbery]]\'\', under the ownership of some security guards in [[Palm Hills]].\n\nA Trainer\'s Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[EP152|Hot Matches!]]\'\'.\n\nA Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[EP169|Beauty and the Breeder]]\'\', under the ownership of a {{tc|Pokémon Breeder}} participating in [[Pokémon Beauty Contest|a Pokémon breeding competition]].\n\nA Growlithe, along with an Arcanine, acted as security guards for a penthouse in \'\'[[HS12|Training Daze]]\'\'.\n\nMultiple Growlithe appeared in the opening sequence of \'\'[[M07|Destiny Deoxys]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[AG159|Off the Unbeaten Path]]\'\', where it was seen participating in the [[Pokémon Orienteering]] competition.\n\nA {{pkmn|Coordinator}}\'s Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[AG167|What I Did for Love!]]\'\'.\n\nA Coordinator\'s Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[AG191|Once More With Reeling!]]\'\', where it was seen participating in the {{to|Terracotta}} {{pkmn|Contest}}.\n\nA Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[DP010|Not on MY Watch Ya Don\'t!]]\'\'.\n\nA Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[DP029|The Champ Twins!]]\'\'.\n\nA Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[DP088|Camping It Up!]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[BW103|Curtain Up, Unova League!]]\'\' and \'\'[[BW105|Lost at the League!]]\'\'.\n\nA Growlithe appeared in a flashback in \'\'[[BW118|Secrets From Out of the Fog!]]\'\'.\n\nA Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[BW138|Go, Go Gogoat!]]\'\' as a resident of an {{OBP|unnamed island|BW138}} in the [[Decolore Islands]].\n\nA Growlithe appeared in [[BWS01]].\n\nA Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[M19|Volcanion and the Mechanical Marvel]]\'\'.\n\nTwo Trainers Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[SM001|Alola to New Adventure!]]\'\'.\n\nA Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[SM004|First Catch in Alola, Ketchum-Style!]]\'\', where it was seen happily giving some {{Berries}} to a group of {{DL|Recurring wild Pokémon in the anime|Pikipek}}.\n\nSix Trainers\' Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[SM006|A Shocking Grocery Run!]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[SM007|That\'s Why the Litten is a Scamp!]]\'\'.\n\nTwo Trainers\' Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[SM009|To Top a Totem!]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[SM013|Racing to a Big Event!]]\'\', where it participated in the [[Pokémon Pancake Race]].\n\nA Trainer\'s Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[SM016|They Might Not Be Giants!]]\'\'.\n\nTwo Trainers\' Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[SM017|Crystal-Clear Sleuthing!]]\'\'.\n\nTwo Trainers\' Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[SM021|One Journey Ends, Another Begins...]]\'\'.\n\nTwo Trainers\' Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[SM023|Getting the Band Back Together!]]\'\'.\n\nTwo Trainers\' Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[SM027|A Glaring Rivalry!]]\'\'. One of them reappeared in a flashback in \'\'[[SM047|A Masked Warning!]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[M20|I Choose You!]]\'\'.\n\nFour Trainers\' Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[SM034|A Crowning Moment of Truth!]]\'\', with one appearing in a flashback. They were among the Pokémon attending the [[Wela Fire Festival\u200e]].\n\nA Trainer\'s Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[SM040|Balloons, Brionne, and Belligerence!]]\'\'.\n\nTwo Trainers\' Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[SM042|Alola, Kanto!]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[SM050|Faba\'s Revenge!]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Growlithe appeared in the [[Banned episodes|banned episode]] [[SM064]].\n\nA Trainer\'s Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[SM067|Love at First Twirl!]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[SM072|Sours for the Sweet!]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[M21|The Power of Us]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[SM082|All They Want to Do is Dance Dance!]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[SM084|The Shape of Love to Come!]]\'\'.\n\nA Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[SM086|I Choose Paradise!]]\'\', where it was among the Pokémon seen at the [[Pokémon Paradise Resort]].\n\nA Trainer\'s Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[SM090|Securing the Future!]]\'\', where it joined the rest of [[Alola]] in showering {{DL|Light trio (anime)|Necrozma}} with light so it could return to its {{DL|List of Pokémon with form differences|Necrozma|normal form}}.\n\nTwo Trainers\' Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[SM099|We Know Where You\'re Going, Eevee!]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[SM112|Got Meltan?]]\'\'.\n\nA student\'s Growlithe appeared in \'\'[[SM119|Aiming for the Top Floor!]]\'\'.\n\nTwo Trainers\' Growlithe appeared in